node.text:
Tag a bestie you would try this with! 🤯🔥 Get your photos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting tripfever.net 👉🏼 the link is in our bio: @tripfever 

You can swing by yourself or tandem with a friend - forwards, backwards, upside down - up to you. You’ll complete the 300m free-fall arc surrounded by @nature.

📽 @jessica_juarezz
📍 Nevis Swing, New Zealand
🎶 Indian Summer - Jai Wolf

node.text:
Mont-Saint-Michel, France 😍 You can check how to get your photos promoted in our account, use the link in our bio @tripfever

Who would you want to visit with?

It has the distinction of being erected on a rocky tidal island, surrounded by a magnificent bay. The Mount and its bay are listed as World Heritage by UNESCO. This grandiose spot, located 3 and a half hours from Paris, is one of the most famous and visited landmark in France.

📽 @_pifou
📍 Mont-Saint-Michel, Normandy, France

True love ❤️ You can check how to get your photos promoted in our account, use the link in our bio @tripfever 

“Choose the person in your life who has the power to make you feel like you're floating.” ❤️ – Cintia Zanuni lifts her up her husband who can’t stand on his own so they can appreciate this magical view together. This story is the ray of sunshine we need in our lives, encouraging us to always embark on new adventures and discover the world with the ones we love the most.

Videos and caption by @cinthiazanuni & @hugoecinthia

node.text:
When a city becomes your boulder ⛰ You can check how to get your photos promoted in our account, use the link in our bio @tripfever

Bouldering is a form of free climbing that is performed on small rock formations or artificial rock walls without the use of ropes or harnesses. While bouldering can be done without any equipment, most climbers use climbing shoes to help secure footholds, chalk to keep their hands dry and to provide a firmer grip, and bouldering mats to prevent injuries from falls. Unlike free solo climbing, which is also performed without ropes, bouldering problems (the sequence of moves that a climber performs to complete the climb) are usually less than 6 meters (20 ft.) tall.

📽 @oliver_thorpe
📍 Aarhus, Denmark

@Nature's most spectacular light show via @imikegraphics 💫 We can promote your photos in our account. Check the link in our bio for instructions: @tripfever

To see the Northern Lights you need dark skies and the season to watch it usually spans early-April until late-August.

Thanks to longer hours of darkness and clear night skies, December through March is usually the best time to observe this elusive @nature phenomenon. 🇫🇮

From 1-8, which is your favorite photo? 💙

📸 @imikegraphics
📍 Lapland, Finland

Would you dare to pass through this Via Ferrata? 😳 You can check how to get your photos promoted in our account, use the link in our bio @tripfever

The new Via Ferrata Delle Aquile, on the top of Paganella, is a highly emotional and spectacular via ferrata that gives you unforgettable emotions; the sight embraces whole Trentino, but keeping fixed on the track too.

Recommendation:
Avoid the queue: purchase online your ticket and go directly to turnstile. Choose the stage and pay with your credit card. You will receive by email your ticket (you can print the ticket or save it in your smartphone), scan it on the orange scanner on the turnstile located at the gates of the lift.

📽 @niklaskoessel
📍Trentino, Italy
